(30, 226, '2012 Terry Fox Run in Vietnam', '', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Terry Fox Run is a commemoration of the dream of Terry Fox, a young Canadian bone cancer patient with an amputated right leg, who wanted to raise money for cancer research by running across Canada. Although Terry died of cancer before he could complete his Marathon of Hope, every year in his memory Terry Fox Runs are held in 51 countries around the world to raise money for cancer research.&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;In 2006, more than 14,000 people participated in the Terry Fox Runs in Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City and 742 million VND was raised. It is a fun, non-competitive event in which you walk, jog, or run a distance of your choice. Participants are encouraged to contribute personal donation and/or seek sponsorship from those unable to attend and/or buy Terry Fox t-shirts; all money will go towards cancer research projects led by the Hanoi Cancer Hospital and Ho Chi Minh Cancer Centre.&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/IMG_0917.jpg&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;598&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/IMG_0929.jpg&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;598&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/IMG_0936.jpg&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;598&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/IMG_0938.jpg&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;598&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/1353823746274.jpg&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;512&quot; height=&quot;288&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '1797', '', 2, 1335336666, 0, 1, '2012 terry fox run in vietnam'),
